A R E S O L U T I O N
To request the Secretary of the Air Force select the 1
121st Air Refueling Wing at the Rickenbacker Air 2
National Guard Base in Columbus, Ohio, as the 3
preferred main operating base for the KC-46 Pegasus 4
refueling aircraft. 5
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
OHIO:
WHEREAS, The Rickenbacker Air National Guard Base has a 6
host of assets that will provide the Air Force and its guard 7
component with unmatched benefits for basing the KC-46; and 8
WHEREAS, Rickenbacker, unmatched in capabilities, features 9
two 12,000-foot runways rated for unrestricted heavy aircraft 10
use. The Columbus Regional Airport Authority, the civilian local 11
airport agency that hosts the 121st ARW, has invested more than 12
$62.9 million in airport infrastructure since 2017, including 13
runway upgrades; and 14
